  "text": "The authoritative Go source files in the distributed etcd service that define and return the error string 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' are located in the main branch of the etcd-io/etcd repository. The ErrCompacted error variable is defined in server/storage/mvcc/kvstore.go as errors.New(\"mvcc: required revision has been compacted\"). This error is returned when a client requests a revision that has been garbage-collected by compaction. The core function rangeKeys, which is responsible for handling range queries on key-value pairs in the MVCC storage layer, is located in server/storage/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go. The rangeKeys function is a method of the storeTxnRead struct and returns this error when the requested revision is less than the first available (non-compacted) revision. The error occurs in the context of MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) range operations when attempting to read at a revision that has been compacted away by the database compaction process, which is a normal operational behavior in etcd that periodically removes historical data to manage storage space."
}

